<div class="guide-layout">

  {{!-- Main Content Area --}}
  <div class="guide-main">

    {{!-- Scrollable Content --}}
    <div class="guide-content">

      {{!-- STEP 1: Welcome --}}
      <div class="guide-panel {{#if (eq activeStep 1)}}active{{/if}}" data-step="1">
        <div class="guide-credits-text">Game Design &amp; Rules By Monolith Studio</div>
        <div class="guide-vtt-credit">Fan Made VTT Sheet by Antonio</div>
        <div class="guide-credits-banner"></div>

        <h2 class="guide-heading">Welcome to the Hyborian Age</h2>

        {{!-- Section: Introduction --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <p class="guide-text">
            Welcome, adventurer, to the savage world of Conan! This guide will walk you through
            creating your character step by step.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-text">
            <strong>Tip:</strong> Click the numbered tabs on the right to jump to any section,
            or use the Next/Back buttons below to progress through the guide.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Let me tell you of the days of high adventure, when the world was young
            and heroes strode the earth..."
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: What You'll Need --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">What You'll Need</h3>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li>Your character sheet (open behind this window)</li>
            <li>A concept for your character's background</li>
            <li>16 stat points to distribute</li>
            <li>3 starting XP to spend on skills</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Overview --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Creation Overview</h3>
          <ol class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Character Settings</strong> — Name, origin, portrait</li>
            <li><strong>Stats</strong> — Distribute 16 points across Might, Edge, Grit, Wits</li>
            <li><strong>Origin Bonuses</strong> — Apply your origin's special abilities</li>
            <li><strong>Skills &amp; XP</strong> — Spend 3 XP on starting skills</li>
            <li><strong>Sorcery</strong> — Learn spells (if your origin grants them)</li>
            <li><strong>Equipment</strong> — Arm yourself with weapons and armor</li>
            <li><strong>Combat Basics</strong> — Understand how to fight and survive</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- STEP 2: Character Settings --}}
      <div class="guide-panel {{#if (eq activeStep 2)}}active{{/if}}" data-step="2">
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Character Settings</h2>

        {{!-- Section: Name Your Character --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Name Your Character</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Click the <strong>settings cog</strong> in the top-right of your character sheet.
            There, you shall inscribe your name into the annals of the Hyborian Age.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "A name carries weight in these lands, young one. Choose wisely, for it shall be
            whispered in taverns and shouted across battlefields..."
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Choose Your Origin --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Choose Your Origin</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Your origin shapes who you are. Select one from the dropdown in character settings.
          </p>
          <ul class="guide-originSimple">
            <li><strong>From the Hills</strong> — Hardy folk forged beyond civilization's edge.</li>
            <li><strong>From the Streets</strong> — Born to muck and larceny in the city's shadow.</li>
            <li><strong>From the Steppes</strong> — Where the rider rules beneath endless sky.</li>
            <li><strong>From the North</strong> — Reavers and sailors, hard as northern ice.</li>
            <li><strong>From the Wilds</strong> — The untamed lands shaped you into something primal.</li>
            <li><strong>From a Civilized Land</strong> — Decadent cities, but never safe.</li>
            <li><strong>From Parts Unknown</strong> — Your past is yours alone to keep.</li>
            <li><strong>Blood of Jhebbal Sag</strong> — The old wild blood runs in your veins.</li>
            <li><strong>Blood of Acheron</strong> — Ancient sorcerous power awakens within.</li>
            <li><strong>Blood of a Demon</strong> — Balanced between human and inhuman.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "From whence do you hail? The answer shapes your destiny, your strengths,
            and the dark paths that may open before you..."
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Derived Values Note --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Life, Armor &amp; More</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Your <strong>Life Points</strong>, <strong>Armor Rating</strong>,
            <strong>Initiative</strong>, and <strong>Conditions</strong> will be addressed
            in later steps. For now, focus on who you are.
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Portrait & Token --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Portrait &amp; Token</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Set your portrait and token image in character settings. Your GM may assist with this.
            If no image is ready, you may return to this later.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "A warrior's visage tells much. Whether scarred by battle or untouched by blade,
            let your image speak of the tales yet to come..."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- STEP 3: Stats & Derived Values --}}
      <div class="guide-panel {{#if (eq activeStep 3)}}active{{/if}}" data-step="3">
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Distribute Stats</h2>

        {{!-- Section: The Four Stats --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">The Four Stats</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            You have <strong>16 points</strong> to distribute. Each stat must be between
            <strong>1</strong> and <strong>5</strong> at creation (can reach 8 later with skills).
          </p>

          <div class="guide-statGrid">
            {{#each stats}}
            <div class="guide-statCard">
              <div class="guide-statCard-name">{{this.name}}</div>
              <div class="guide-statCard-desc">{{this.description}}</div>
            </div>
            {{/each}}
          </div>

          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Strength of arm, swiftness of blade, endurance of spirit, cunning of mind—
            these are the pillars upon which a warrior is built..."
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Flex and Defense --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Flex and Defense</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Open the <strong>cog wheel</strong> on your defense section to configure your
            Flex Die and manage your defenses.
          </p>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Flex Die:</strong> Starts at d10 and can be improved to d8 or d6 via XP.</li>
            <li><strong>Physical Defense:</strong> Calculated automatically from your stats by default.</li>
            <li><strong>Sorcery Defense:</strong> Calculated automatically from your stats by default.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Defenses are <strong>locked</strong> by default and will auto-calculate.
            Click the lock icon to unlock a defense if you need to manually override its value.
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Derived Values --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Derived Values</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            The following values are calculated automatically from your stats and origin:
          </p>

          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Life Points (LP):</strong> (Grit × 2) + Origin Base LP + Skill bonuses</li>
            <li><strong>Stamina Points (SP):</strong> Equal to your Grit stat (resets each Tale)</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "The body's resilience and the quickness of reflexes decide whether
            you walk from the fray... or are carried from it."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- STEP 4: Origin Bonuses --}}
      <div class="guide-panel {{#if (eq activeStep 4)}}active{{/if}}" data-step="4">
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Origin Bonuses</h2>

        {{!-- Section: Your Birthright --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Your Birthright</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Each origin grants unique bonuses. Navigate to the <strong>Origin tab</strong> on your
            character sheet to see and manage these abilities.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Where you come from shapes what you become. The hills breed warriors,
            the streets breed survivors, the bloodlines breed... something else entirely..."
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Skill Choices --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Starting Skill Choices</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Some origins offer a choice between starting skills. If yours does,
            you'll see buttons to select which skill you want. This choice is permanent.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-text">
            <strong>Note:</strong> Origin skills are free—they don't cost XP. They represent
            abilities you've developed from your background.
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Stat Bonuses --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Per-Tale Bonuses</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Origins like "From the Hills" let you choose a stat bonus at the start of each Tale.
            Check your Origin tab to make this selection when starting a new adventure.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Some gifts are constant, others must be chosen anew with each rising sun.
            Adapt to the challenges before you..."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- STEP 5: Skills & XP --}}
      <div class="guide-panel {{#if (eq activeStep 5)}}active{{/if}}" data-step="5">
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Skills &amp; XP</h2>

        {{!-- Section: Starting XP --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Your Starting XP</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            You begin with <strong>3 XP</strong> that must be spent before your first adventure.
            Navigate to the <strong>Skills tab</strong> to spend your XP.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Experience is the coin of survival. Spend it wisely, for the Hyborian Age
            does not suffer fools gladly..."
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Skill Categories --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Skill Categories</h3>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Starting Skills (1-3 XP):</strong> Basic abilities available to new characters</li>
            <li><strong>Legendary Skills (1-6 XP):</strong> Powerful abilities for experienced heroes</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: How to Buy --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Buying Skills</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Click the <strong>Add Skill</strong> button to open the skill menu. Skills you can afford
            are highlighted. Click a skill to purchase it—the XP cost is deducted automatically.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-text">
            <strong>Rule:</strong> During play, you can only learn one new skill per Respite
            (rest period between adventures).
          </p>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "A warrior learns in blood and fire. Each new trick, each mastered technique,
            is carved into your very being..."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- STEP 6: Sorcery --}}
      <div class="guide-panel {{#if (eq activeStep 6)}}active{{/if}}" data-step="6">
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Sorcery</h2>

        {{!-- Section: Dark Arts --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">The Dark Arts</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Not all origins grant access to sorcery. If yours does, navigate to the
            <strong>Sorcery tab</strong> to manage your magical abilities.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Sorcery is a blade with no hilt. It cuts the wielder as surely as the foe.
            Are you prepared to pay its price in blood and soul?"
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Disciplines --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Sorcery Disciplines</h3>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Alchemy</strong> — Potions, transmutation, animated constructs</li>
            <li><strong>Black Magic</strong> — Fear, shadows, illusions, curses</li>
            <li><strong>Demonic Magic</strong> — Hellfire, fiends, infernal power</li>
            <li><strong>Necromantic Magic</strong> — Death, undead, life drain</li>
            <li><strong>White Magic</strong> — Healing, nature, beasts, protection</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Casting --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Casting Spells</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Spells cost Life Points and/or Stamina Points to cast. Once purchased with XP,
            a spell is always available—no preparation needed. If you have the LP/SP, you can cast it.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-text">
            <strong>Inherent Spells:</strong> Each discipline grants three inherent spells
            for free when you gain access to that discipline.
          </p>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "The words of power tear at your very life force. Each incantation
            is a bargain made with forces beyond mortal ken..."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- STEP 7: Weapons & Armor --}}
      <div class="guide-panel {{#if (eq activeStep 7)}}active{{/if}}" data-step="7">
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Arm Up</h2>

        {{!-- Section: Weapons --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Choose Your Weapons</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            You can carry up to <strong>3 weapons</strong>, or <strong>2 if using a shield</strong>.
            Navigate to the <strong>Arms tab</strong> to equip yourself.
          </p>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Melee</strong> — Swords, axes, maces (Might for attack and damage)</li>
            <li><strong>Thrown</strong> — Daggers, javelins (Edge for attack, Might for damage)</li>
            <li><strong>Ranged</strong> — Bows, crossbows (Edge for attack, no stat for damage)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Steel speaks a language all its own. Choose blades that suit your nature,
            for they shall become extensions of your will..."
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Armor --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Armor &amp; Protection</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Armor provides an Armor Rating (AR) that reduces incoming damage. Heavier armor
            protects more but imposes penalties to sorcery and stealth.
          </p>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Unarmored:</strong> AR 0, no penalties</li>
            <li><strong>Light (Hide/Leather):</strong> AR 3, -1 sorcery/stealth</li>
            <li><strong>Medium (Breastplate):</strong> AR 5, -2 sorcery/stealth, max 2 moves</li>
            <li><strong>Heavy (Full Plate):</strong> AR 8, -3 sorcery/stealth, max 1 move, 1 recovery</li>
            <li><strong>Shield:</strong> +1 Physical Defense, requires one hand</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Plate may turn a blade, but it slows the step. Leather breathes with
            the warrior's flesh. Choose what serves your path..."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- STEP 8: Combat Overview --}}
      <div class="guide-panel {{#if (eq activeStep 8)}}active{{/if}}" data-step="8">
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Combat Basics</h2>

        {{!-- Section: Making Attacks --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Making Attacks</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Roll <strong>Stat Die + Stat Value + Modifiers</strong> vs the target's Defense.
            Equal or exceed their defense to hit and roll damage.
          </p>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Melee:</strong> Might Die + Might vs Physical Defense</li>
            <li><strong>Ranged/Thrown:</strong> Edge Die + Edge vs Physical Defense</li>
            <li><strong>Sorcery:</strong> Wits Die + Wits vs Sorcery Defense</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Combat in the Hyborian Age is swift and brutal. Hesitate, and you die.
            Strike true, and your enemy falls..."
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: The Flex Die --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">The Flex Die</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Every roll includes a <strong>Flex Die</strong> (starts at d10). Rolling the maximum
            value grants special effects:
          </p>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Stamina:</strong> Gain 1 SP</li>
            <li><strong>Success:</strong> Turn a failed roll into a success</li>
            <li><strong>Massive Damage:</strong> Add max weapon die to damage</li>
            <li><strong>Sorcery:</strong> Regain spell's LP/SP cost</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Stamina Spends --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Stamina Spends</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Stamina Points fuel special abilities in combat:
          </p>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>1 SP:</strong> +1 to die roll, bonus move, +1d4 damage, extend thrown range</li>
            <li><strong>2 SP:</strong> +2 to die roll, +2d4 damage</li>
            <li><strong>Final SP:</strong> Apply Massive Damage effect</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="guide-narrator">
            "Stamina is the fire in your veins. Burn it wisely, for when it fades,
            so too does your edge in battle..."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {{!-- STEP 9: Final Overview --}}
      <div class="guide-panel {{#if (eq activeStep 9)}}active{{/if}}" data-step="9">
        <h2 class="guide-heading">Ready for Adventure</h2>

        {{!-- Section: Checklist --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Character Checklist</h3>
          <p class="guide-text">
            Before you venture forth, ensure you have completed each step:
          </p>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Name:</strong> Have you named your character?</li>
            <li><strong>Origin:</strong> Have you selected an origin?</li>
            <li><strong>Stats:</strong> Have you distributed all 16 stat points?</li>
            <li><strong>Origin Bonuses:</strong> Have you made any required origin choices?</li>
            <li><strong>Skills:</strong> Have you spent your 3 starting XP?</li>
            <li><strong>Weapons:</strong> Have you equipped at least one weapon?</li>
            <li><strong>Armor:</strong> Have you selected your armor type?</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Quick Reference --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <h3 class="guide-subheading">Quick Reference</h3>
          <ul class="guide-list">
            <li><strong>Actions per Turn:</strong> 2 (Move, Attack, Defend, Cast, etc.)</li>
            <li><strong>Focused Attack:</strong> 2 Actions for +2 to Attack</li>
            <li><strong>Defend:</strong> 1 Action for +2 Physical Defense until next turn</li>
            <li><strong>Recovery:</strong> 2 per Tale (1 with Heavy Armor), regain 50% max LP + 1 SP</li>
            <li><strong>Death:</strong> At 0 LP, pass Grit Check (Diff 8) or die</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="guide-text">
            <strong>Tip:</strong> Reopen this guide anytime by clicking the guide
            button at the bottom of your character sheet's tab bar.
          </p>
        </div>

        {{!-- Section: Final Words --}}
        <div class="guide-section">
          <p class="guide-narrator" style="text-align: center; border-left: none; background: transparent; padding: 16px;">
            "Know, O prince, that between the years when the oceans drank Atlantis and the
            gleaming cities, and the years of the rise of the Sons of Aryas, there was an Age
            undreamed of... And unto this world you are born. A thief, a reaver, a slayer—
            with gigantic melancholies and gigantic mirth. Go forth, and carve your legend
            into the stones of the Hyborian Age."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    {{!-- Navigation Bar --}}
    <div class="guide-nav">
      <button type="button" class="guide-navBtn prev" {{#if isFirstStep}}disabled{{/if}}>
        &larr; Back
      </button>

      <span class="guide-stepIndicator">Step {{activeStep}} of {{totalSteps}}</span>

      <button type="button" class="guide-navBtn next" {{#if isLastStep}}disabled{{/if}}>
        Next &rarr;
      </button>
    </div>

  </div>

